<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05032n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05032n">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05032n"> 32(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> manna of holy doctrine / wage holy war</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;Coming there as was his custom,&rsquo; says, adding that his object in these visits was to see Martin and the servants of God, who, under Martin&apos;s guidance, <mark>waged the Holy War</mark>. &lsquo;He went there also,&rsquo; says the legend, &lsquo;to seek for spiritual consolations, and to join with the brethren in offering the sacrifice of the Immaculate Lamb.&rsquo; Upon on of these occasions, &lsquo;after sweet converse and having fed the brethren with <mark>the manna of holy doctrine</mark>, the Pontiff set out for Poitiers, Martin accompaying him &hellip;.&rsquo; <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 31</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
